 Despite the pandemic-induced impacts, in the first 10 months of this year, Tangshan Port handled 95.98 million tonnes of coal, up 7.3 percent year on year. Tangshan, which is 150 km from Beijing and sits on the north of the Bohai Sea, links 39 inland ports in nine provinces of China and more than 190 ports in over 70 nations and regions.  Produced by Xinhua Global Service 